From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 06:51:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] provenance: opt-in --vars; record rhs, dereferences, and
 execution context
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Variable tracing is now OPT-IN: `sarun run --vars` (exports
SARUN_TRACE_VARS=1 into the box; both recorders early-return without
it) — a yocto-scale build pays nothing by default.

Each makevar row additionally records HOW the assignment looked and
what fed it: the UNEXPANDED rhs text (kati stmt.orig_rhs / brush's
assignment AST, capped 1KB) and the variable names it dereferences
(text scan; make function heads excluded, $(call NAME,…)/$(value
NAME) count their first argument) — plus its execution context: the
recipe edge's primary output and the enclosing pipeline uid (a
builtin sub-make parses on the invoking recipe's thread, so its
assignments anchor to the spawning edge). review.makevars resolves
those anchors to build_edges/brushprov row ids in the same query and
grows an any-mode (OR name/value) for single-term searches. The kati
hook also reports the ASSIGNMENT site (+= points at the append, not
the original :=).

test_make_rs.py case 24 covers rhs/refs, edge anchoring of shell and
sub-make assignments, and that an untraced box records zero rows.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01B97aMMA3rHQW7gsyBB2Cpa
---
 src/interp.rs | 10 ++++++----
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/interp.rs b/src/interp.rs
index 091a091..08bd338 100644
--- a/src/interp.rs
+++ b/src/interp.rs
@@ -1544,7 +1544,8 @@ async fn expand_assignment_value(
 // interpreter applies — (name, value, exported). The embedding engine records
 // them (tagged with its recipe/pipeline context) into the box's capture DB so
 // make↔shell↔sub-make variable flows are traceable from one searchable place.
-pub type AssignObserver = std::sync::Arc<dyn Fn(&str, &str, bool) + Send + Sync>;
+/// (name, expanded value, exported, UNEXPANDED assignment text)
+pub type AssignObserver = std::sync::Arc<dyn Fn(&str, &str, bool, &str) + Send + Sync>;
 
 static ASSIGN_OBSERVER: std::sync::RwLock<Option<AssignObserver>> =
     std::sync::RwLock::new(None);
@@ -1559,9 +1560,9 @@ fn assign_observer() -> Option<AssignObserver> {
 
 /// Report one assignment to the installed observer — for builtins that set
 /// variables outside apply_assignment (export/declare).
-pub fn observe_assignment(name: &str, value: &str, exported: bool) {
+pub fn observe_assignment(name: &str, value: &str, exported: bool, rhs: &str) {
     if let Some(obs) = assign_observer() {
-        obs(name, value, exported);
+        obs(name, value, exported, rhs);
     }
 }
 
@@ -1634,7 +1635,8 @@ async fn apply_assignment(
 
     // sarun: report to the installed assignment observer (engine capture).
     if let Some(obs) = assign_observer() {
-        obs(variable_name.as_str(), &new_value.to_string(), export);
+        obs(variable_name.as_str(), &new_value.to_string(), export,
+            &assignment.to_string());
     }
 
     // See if we need to eval an array index.
